[09:31.33]	'Tis very true, my grief lies all within;
[09:35.46]	And these external manners of laments
[09:39.50]	Are merely shadows to the unseen grief
[09:43.62]	That swells with silence in the tortured soul;
[09:48.39]	There lies the substance: and I thank thee, king,
